TY  - JOUR
AU  - Pichler, Pegaret
AU  - Stomper, Alex
AU  - Zulehner, Christine
T1  - Why Leverage Affects Pricing
PY  - 2008
Y1  - 2008/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhn048
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 21
IS  - 4
SP  - 1733
EP  - 1765
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We explain and provide evidence for effects of leverage on pricing. Our model identifies two effects that either counteract or reinforce each other, depending on the debt maturity structure: (i) firms set higher prices (underinvest in market share) if they have more debt, and (ii) firms engage in dynamic risk-shifting by setting lower (higher) prices if the current debt obligation will be higher (lower) in the next period than in the present period. Using a unique dataset of owner-managed hotels in Austrian ski resorts, we provide empirical evidence of both effects.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhn048
ER  - 



