TY  - JOUR
AU  - Welch, Ivo
AU  - Goyal, Amit
T1  - A Comprehensive Look at The Empirical Performance of Equity Premium Prediction
PY  - 2008
Y1  - 2008/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhm014
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 21
IS  - 4
SP  - 1455
EP  - 1508
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Our article comprehensively reexamines the performance of variables that have been suggested by the academic literature to be good predictors of the equity premium. We find that by and large, these models have predicted poorly both in-sample (IS) and out-of-sample (OOS) for 30 years now; these models seem unstable, as diagnosed by their out-of-sample predictions and other statistics; and these models would not have helped an investor with access only to available information to profitably time the market.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhm014
ER  - 



